		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p103568">Just an update</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Juneia</strong> &raquo; Sat May 28, 2005 7:11 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">Again i cant say this enough. The amount of support i have gotten from this community is staggering. There was so much invested interest from people here on the boards, like Yakk and Cailech and others who gave words of advice an strats, to countless people ingame offering their assistance. 
<br />
<br />I almost daily still look at this thread. Remembering her, remembering how much the world truly is not such a lonely or aweful place as we see so often flooded from popular media.
<br />
<br />So sadly i just have not been able to log back on since i completed the epic. When i did the final turn in with Jeb in BW, i was so relieved. I mean i had worked at a fevered pace for three days with little sleep finishing it. And at my age chickies, thats nothin to sniff at. Hell i drop into slumber if a soft breeze blows in the correct direction. But when i gated out and landed back in PoK, i just emotionally sank. The whole situation hit me, maybe because Everquest was such a focus for our lives that I said out loud again, "Now what?" I  had a small idea to create a guild in her name, calling it "Juneia" maybe to bring back some of her love and kindness to EQ. To maybe have people carry on in her name, simply logging on to our game an seeking to help others, with a quest like my own, or companionship, or even something so simple as a kind word from someone who cares. The thought almost took hold, as i imagined that tag running all over the server and people with no more greater purpose then in search of just being of assistance to someone who desperatly needed it. Like june used to do.
<br />
<br />The anserwer though with some tears and shaking hands was nothing. Nothing was left, not without her. So i said goodbye to that beautiful human female, with golden hair the color of the sun and robes to match. I said goodbye to June, and it felt like I was saying goodbye all over again. 
<br />I still visit her stone everyday and talk to her for a couple hours, telling her about the kids and grandkids and what not. I know shes listening.
<br />
<br />But life goes on does it not? And even for a 76 year old fuddy like me. But things have become easier of course with time. I spend most of my free time with my children and their children. PLaying baseball with the babies, watching them repeatedly kick my butt at Playstation2, or telling them stories about grammy in her younger days. 
<br />
<br />So they have now become my hobby. I am not so nieve to believe that my time left on this world is infinte. So i resolved to leaving my family with the best things i can. Guidance from our generation for my now adult children, and warm and wonderful memories for our grandchildren of a happy childhood. I know that when it is my time, my goals will be complete and my family will be equipped for any challenges they may face in the future. With Junes guidance of course, (who else could it be?)
<br />
<br />So again thank you Runes and EQ Community. I didnt realize it at the time but finishing this for June became as important to do for myself as it was originally for Juneia. Maybe because i needed to hold onto a piece of her for just a little longer and slowly let it go on my own time, rather then by suprise.  But without your support, part of my healing would never have happened. 
<br />
<br />So to you I (and June) officially sign off of Everquest with my most heart felt gratitude for each an everyone of you. 
<br />
<br />Goodbye.
<br />
<br />From Babien (Bob)  and Juneia Filice 
<br />
<br />PS. If anyone ever sees Eadric please tell him that I know how much he has hurt from her loss, he wanted to fly down an stay with me for her funeral but he simply couldnt because of financial reasons. I have tried to call him on different occasions but have been unable to contact him. If anyone does speak with him please let him know that June loved him as her own son. Even i wasnt with her when she passed on, Ead was (spiritually) as june always kept his picture framed on her nightstand and told him hello every morning. She loved him so much and i dont think he has been able to recover well from this. It is my sincere hope Eadric is well.</div>

			

		</div>

		
